isition of a third language. On the other hand, studies in interlanguage pragmatics have taken into account variables affecting the use of request acts by second language learners of English. The two research areas are connected in this volume, as it deals with bilingualism effects in the pragmatic production and awareness of third language learners of English. The first part of the book includes a theoretical description of research conducted in the areas of third language acquisition and interlanguage pragmatics, and the second part presents a detailed description of the empirical study carried out in a multilingual speech community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aConscience linguistiquexValencia <Autonome Region>xEnglisch. 0aLangage et languesxÉtude et enseignement. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguage awareness. 0aPragmatics. 0aPragmatique. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aBilingualism .  aELLs.  aEnglish language learner.  aL3 acquisition.  aMultilingualism.  aforeign language acquisition.  apragmatics .  asecond language learners.  athird language acquisition.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359804340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853598043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853598043/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA